          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation, study and recitation and is a late Vedic philosophical treatise employing primarily mantras (words or phrases of power), especially the mantra Oṃ. The work outlines four states of consciousness (awake, dreaming, sleeping, and transcendent) and is the shortest among the Upaniṣads with 12 verses.</summary>
